{"TopicId":144694,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Apollo Capsule-a-like","CreatedByName":"Bloojay","CreatedById":162865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T22:22:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Bloojay","CreatedById":162865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T22:22:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a simple build I use for my Apollo-Like missions, because the top of the Capsule has that ring, it makes putting a docking port directly on top of it look kinda broken. So this is what i do to get around it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(taken from my post about it in the open source construction techniques thread)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222693833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002239663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469657154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162865\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bloojay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is how I construct my Apollo-a-like command capsule:\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Imgur album:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/ZFhwT\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/ZFhwT\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221H686oEh.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/1H686oEh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe basic componetns, a .65 to 1.25m structural adapter, and a docking port are the main components, attached to a capsule of course\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fCjxzvRh.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/fCjxzvRh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsmush \u0027em down\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KZordq9h.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/KZordq9h.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice \u0027n flush\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022okZuchYh.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/okZuchYh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis is how i do my Launch escape system and shroud\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222HMd7lHh.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/2HMd7lHh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts just more historically accurate and sleeker. Its done in 2 segments, the first extending downward and out, parallel to the capsule,\u003Cbr\u003E\nand then cuts in and finishes connected to the Heat-Shielding, decoupler, Or even the capsule if done correctly.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt may result in less than pretty edges, this is easily resolved with offsetting the entire fairing upwards a smidge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T22:27:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222693858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469658136\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162865\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bloojay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Bloojay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild a Saturn V and LM!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bloojay","CreatedById":162865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T23:03:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshov